  },
  {
    id: 'cockpit-portfolio',
    title: 'XENO SPACESHIP',
    subtitle: 'Immersive portfolio system',
    description: 'A sci-fi portfolio experience inspired by alien spacecraft, old movie interfaces, and the strange sleekness of xenomorph design.',
    status: 'Live portfolio',
    cover: '/assets/cockpitthumbnaipc.avif',
    hero: '/assets/cockpitthumbnaipc.avif',
    tech: ['Astro', 'TypeScript', 'CSS', 'Canvas', 'Responsive UI'],
    oneLine: 'A portfolio built as an interactive xeno spacecraft instead of a traditional scrolling site.',
    metrics: [
      { label: 'Persistent HUD', value: 1, suffix: ' System' },
      { label: 'Sensor Modes', value: 3 },
      { label: 'Core Routes', value: 6 }
    ],
    timeline: '2026',
    story: [
      'I am a big sci-fi nerd, so when I started brainstorming a new idea for my portfolio website, I looked there first for inspiration.',
      'Nothing inspired me more than xenomorphs. I know the Alien films shaped that love, but something about that creature has captivated me since I was a kid: the scale, the weird design, and the way it still feels sleek and almost aerodynamic.',
      'I wanted to build something consistent inside that universe, the kind of old sci-fi ship interface I have always loved.',
      'XENO SPACESHIP is my love letter to those movies: an immersive cockpit where the frame and HUD stay alive while the content shifts inside the canopy.'
    ],
    screenshots: [
      { src: '/assets/cockpitthumbnaipc.avif', label: 'Desktop cockpit layout', type: 'desktop' },
      { src: '/assets/cockpitmobile.avif', label: 'Mobile cockpit layout', type: 'mobile' }
    ],
    responsibilities: ['Frontend Engineering', 'Product Direction', 'UX Design', 'Interaction Design', 'Animation Systems', 'Responsive Design', 'Canvas Starfield', 'Performance Tuning', 'Accessibility', 'Visual System Design'],
    challenges: ['Keeping the cockpit visually rich without relying on heavy shaders, Three.js, or particle libraries.', 'Making persistent HUD components work across desktop and mobile without feeling like normal website widgets.', 'Maintaining clarity and readability while preserving the cinematic spacecraft interface.'],
    learnings: ['A strong interface concept needs consistent component rules or it quickly becomes visual noise.', 'Lightweight CSS, canvas, and careful state management can create a rich product feel without heavy rendering cost.'],
    links: [
      { label: 'View Live Site', href: '/' }
    ]
  }
];

